Use of relic/libsodium namespaces in BLS library. This is not a good practice for C libraries/includes and will cause issues with integrating into larger code bases. See below examples
#if BLSALLOC_SODIUM
namespace libsodium {
    #include "sodium/utils.h"
    #include "sodium/core.h"
}
#endif

namespace relic {
    #include "relic.h"
    #include "relic_test.h"
}
You are trying to wrap C functions/types into C++ namespaces via this method.
The problem is that if any of those includes, includes something like <string.h> , etc, it will wrap those functions/types inside relic too
Then if you later include the same file AFTER that include it will be ignored and you won't be able to access those functions/types from the global (or std:: for example) scope.
I'd recommend removing both of those namespaces. You won't have conflict with c++ code if they use namespaces and you'll only conflict with other C libraries with the same functions/types - which should be pretty rare and might be a problem anyways if the libraries are externally compiled/linked - duplicate symbols
I can do a PR for this if there is agreement

